The paper discusses the fundamental limits of localization accuracy in wireless networks, which involves topics such as signal processing, information theory, networking, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves networking and system aspects, which suggest cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses statistical methods to analyze the localization accuracy, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of waveforms, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
